## API base URL + mock-fallback pattern

```ts
// src/api/index.ts
const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? 'https://api.michaelwegter.com/adverteyes';
const api = axios.create({ baseURL: BASE });
// On 401/network error → clear token, redirect to login
// CRITICAL: wrap ALL calls in try/catch and return mock data on failure (no console errors on first paint)
```

Demo-time `.env` (for local vite dev): `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3741`
Production build uses the default `https://api.michaelwegter.com/adverteyes`.

**Mock data strategy:** Each API module exports a `MOCK_*` constant. On fetch failure (network or 502), return mock. This ensures the demo loads cleanly if Surface is down.

---

## Exact API contracts (extracted from backend source)

### Auth
```
POST /auth/login   { email, password } → { token, user: { id, email, name, role } }
GET  /auth/me      (Bearer) → { user: { id, email, name, role } }
```

### Inventory
```
GET  /inventory              ?type=&status=&search= → { inventory: Unit[] }
GET  /inventory/:id          → { unit: Unit, bookings: Booking[] }
POST /inventory              (admin|sales) { name, type, lat, lng, monthly_rate, ... }
PUT  /inventory/:id          (admin)
DELETE /inventory/:id        (admin)
```
Unit fields: `id, name, type, subtype, location_desc, city, state, lat, lng, width_ft, height_ft, illuminated(0|1), digital(0|1), monthly_rate, weekly_impressions, status, notes`

### Campaigns
```
GET  /campaigns              ?client_id=&status= → { campaigns: Campaign[] }
     (client role sees only their campaigns — server-side filtered to client_id=1)
     Campaign includes: client_name, booking_count, booked_value
GET  /campaigns/:id          → { campaign, bookings }
POST /campaigns              (admin|sales)
PUT  /campaigns/:id          (admin|sales)
```

### Bookings
```
GET  /bookings               ?campaign_id=&unit_id=&status= → { bookings: Booking[] }
     Booking includes: campaign_name, client_name, unit_name, unit_type, city, location_desc
POST /bookings/check-conflict  { unit_id, start_date, end_date } → { conflict: bool, detail: string|null }
POST /bookings               → 201 { id, conflict:false } | 409 { error, conflict:true, detail }
PUT  /bookings/:id           (admin|sales)
DELETE /bookings/:id         (admin) → soft cancel
```

### Users
```
GET  /users                  (admin) → { users: User[] }
POST /users                  (admin) { email, password, name, role }
PUT  /users/:id              (admin) { name, role, active, password? }
```

### Weather
```
GET /weather/:unitId         → {
  unit: { id, name, city, lat, lng },
  current: { temperature, wind_speed, wind_gusts, precipitation, weather_code, weather_desc,
             install_risk:'HIGH'|'LOW', install_risk_reason },
  hourly: { time[], temperature_2m[], wind_speed_10m[], precipitation[], weather_code[], visibility[] },
  timezone, fetched_at
}
```

### Traffic
```
GET /traffic/:unitId         → { currentSpeed, freeFlowSpeed, congestionPct, confidence, roadClosure,
                                  trafficScore, impression_multiplier, source:'tomtom'|'mock', unit:{id,name} }
GET /traffic                 → { traffic: [{id, name, currentSpeed, freeFlowSpeed, congestionPct, ...}] }
```

### Health
```
GET /health → { ok:true, service:'adverteyes-api', ts:... }
```

