## Inventory Leaflet map spec

- Center: Tampa Bay approx `[27.95, -82.46]`, zoom 11
- Marker color per type: billboard=`#FF6B1A` (orange), dooh=`#3B82F6` (blue), truckside=`#EAB308` (yellow)
- Use `L.circleMarker` (not default marker) → avoids icon-path issue entirely; radius 8-12px
- Fill-opacity scales with traffic congestion: `0.5 + (congestionPct/200)` (fetch from `/traffic` batch endpoint)
- Click marker → show asset detail panel (right slide-in `.detail-panel`) with weather+traffic data
- Map toggle: Table view | Map view (`.view-toggle` buttons)

---

## Conflict detection demo flow (Bookings page)

1. Select unit "Dale Mabry & Kennedy" (id=3, currently `booked`)
2. Enter dates overlapping existing Ford Summer booking (2026-06-01 to 2026-08-31)
3. POST `/bookings/check-conflict` → `{ conflict: true, detail: "Conflicts with campaign \"Ford Summer Sales Event\" (2026-06-01 to 2026-08-31)" }`
4. Show `.conflict-alert` div with the detail message
5. Block submit until conflict resolved (different dates or unit)

