## Free API notes

### Open-Meteo (no key, no signup)
URL: `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude={lat}&longitude={lon}&hourly=temperature_2m,wind_speed_10m,wind_gusts_10m,precipitation,weather_code,visibility&current=temperature_2m,wind_speed_10m,wind_gusts_10m,precipitation,weather_code&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&wind_speed_unit=mph&timezone=auto&forecast_days=3`
Already proxied in backend weather route. Frontend calls `/weather/:unitId` — never calls Open-Meteo directly.

### TomTom Traffic Flow (free tier)
Free tier: 2,500 req/day. Signup at developer.tomtom.com → generate API key → set `TOMTOM_API_KEY` in Surface `.env` at `data/runner-workspace/adverteyes-api/.env`.
Backend falls back to realistic deterministic mock when key absent — demo works without the key.
Backend caches 15-min TTL per unit. Frontend calls `/traffic/:unitId` or `/traffic` (batch).

