## Vite tsconfig requirement

`demo-src/tsconfig.json` must include:
```json
"moduleResolution": "Bundler"
```
Without this, react-leaflet ESM imports break. Verify before build.

---

## Surface deployment checklist (demo-builder owns steps 1-4)

1. `python scripts/surface_run.py --lang python --file upwork-runs/adverteyes/surface_build.py`
   - Writes all TS source to Surface `data/runner-workspace/adverteyes-api/`
   - Runs `npm install && npm run build`
   - Success: `[build] Success` + no TS errors
2. `python scripts/surface_run.py --lang python --file upwork-runs/adverteyes/surface_register.py`
   - Registers `adverteyes-api` service, port 3741
   - Success: prints `LISTENING` within ~30s
3. Write `../mw-backend/adverteyes_blueprint.py` (PREFIX=adverteyes, UPSTREAM=http://127.0.0.1:3741)
4. Register in `../mw-backend/server.py`: `from adverteyes_blueprint import bridge_bp; app.register_blueprint(bridge_bp)` — do NOT push
5. Build frontend: `cd demo-src && npm install && npm run build`
6. Verify `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/adverteyes/index.html` exists
7. Add workSamples.js entry

